  "root_text": {
    "snp2.9:0.1": "Sutta Nipāta 2.9 ",
    "snp2.9:0.2": "Kiṁsīlasutta ",
    "snp2.9:1.1": "“Kiṁsīlo kiṁsamācāro, ",
    "snp2.9:1.2": "kāni kammāni brūhayaṁ; ",
    "snp2.9:1.3": "Naro sammā niviṭṭhassa, ",
    "snp2.9:1.4": "uttamatthañca pāpuṇe”. ",
    "snp2.9:2.1": "“Vuḍḍhāpacāyī anusūyako siyā, ",
    "snp2.9:2.2": "Kālaññū cassa garūnaṁ dassanāya; ",
    "snp2.9:2.3": "Dhammiṁ kathaṁ erayitaṁ khaṇaññū, ",
    "snp2.9:2.4": "Suṇeyya sakkacca subhāsitāni. ",
    "snp2.9:3.1": "Kālena gacche garūnaṁ sakāsaṁ, ",
    "snp2.9:3.2": "Thambhaṁ niraṅkatvā nivātavutti; ",
    "snp2.9:3.3": "Atthaṁ dhammaṁ saṁyamaṁ brahmacariyaṁ, ",
    "snp2.9:3.4": "Anussare ceva samācare ca. ",
    "snp2.9:4.1": "Dhammārāmo dhammarato, ",
    "snp2.9:4.2": "Dhamme ṭhito dhammavinicchayaññū; ",
    "snp2.9:4.3": "Nevācare dhammasandosavādaṁ, ",
    "snp2.9:4.4": "Tacchehi nīyetha subhāsitehi. ",
    "snp2.9:5.1": "Hassaṁ jappaṁ paridevaṁ padosaṁ, ",
    "snp2.9:5.2": "Māyākataṁ kuhanaṁ giddhi mānaṁ; ",
    "snp2.9:5.3": "Sārambhaṁ kakkasaṁ kasāvañca mucchaṁ, ",
    "snp2.9:5.4": "Hitvā care vītamado ṭhitatto. ",
    "snp2.9:6.1": "Viññātasārāni subhāsitāni, ",
    "snp2.9:6.2": "Sutañca viññātasamādhisāraṁ; ",
    "snp2.9:6.3": "Na tassa paññā ca sutañca vaḍḍhati, ",
    "snp2.9:6.4": "Yo sāhaso hoti naro pamatto. ",
    "snp2.9:7.1": "Dhamme ca ye ariyapavedite ratā, ",
    "snp2.9:7.2": "Anuttarā te vacasā manasā kammunā ca; ",
    "snp2.9:7.3": "Te santisoraccasamādhisaṇṭhitā, ",
    "snp2.9:7.4": "Sutassa paññāya ca sāramajjhagū”ti. ",
    "snp2.9:7.5": "Kiṁsīlasuttaṁ navamaṁ. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "snp2.9:0.1": "Anthology of Discourses 2.9 ",
    "snp2.9:0.2": "What Morality? ",
    "snp2.9:1.1": "“With what morality, what conduct, ",
    "snp2.9:1.2": "fostering what deeds, ",
    "snp2.9:1.3": "would a person lay the foundations right, ",
    "snp2.9:1.4": "and reach the highest goal?” ",
    "snp2.9:2.1": "“Honoring elders without jealousy, ",
    "snp2.9:2.2": "they’d know the time to visit their teachers. ",
    "snp2.9:2.3": "Treasuring the chance for a Dhamma talk, ",
    "snp2.9:2.4": "they’d listen carefully to the well-spoken words. ",
    "snp2.9:3.1": "At the right time, they’d enter the teacher’s presence ",
    "snp2.9:3.2": "in placid manner, leaving obstinacy behind. ",
    "snp2.9:3.3": "They’d call to mind and put into practice ",
    "snp2.9:3.4": "the meaning, the teaching, self-control, <j>and the spiritual life. ",
    "snp2.9:4.1": "Delighting in the teaching, enjoying the teaching, ",
    "snp2.9:4.2": "standing on the teaching, evaluating the teaching, ",
    "snp2.9:4.3": "they’d never say anything that degraded the teaching, ",
    "snp2.9:4.4": "but would be guided by genuine words well-spoken. ",
    "snp2.9:5.1": "Giving up mirth, muttered prayer, weeping, ill will, ",
    "snp2.9:5.2": "deceit, fawning, greed, conceit, ",
    "snp2.9:5.3": "aggression, crudeness, stains, and indulgence, ",
    "snp2.9:5.4": "they’d wander free of vanity, steadfast. ",
    "snp2.9:6.1": "Understanding is the essence of well-spoken words, ",
    "snp2.9:6.2": "stillness is the essence of learning and understanding. ",
    "snp2.9:6.3": "Wisdom and learning do not flourish ",
    "snp2.9:6.4": "in a hasty and negligent person. ",
    "snp2.9:7.1": "Those happy with the teaching <j>proclaimed by the Noble One ",
    "snp2.9:7.2": "are supreme in speech, mind, and deed. ",
    "snp2.9:7.3": "Abiding in peace, gentleness, and stillness, ",
    "snp2.9:7.4": "they’ve realized the essence of learning and wisdom.” "
  },
  "variant_text": {
    "snp2.9:2.2": "Kālaññū → kālaññu (si, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) | garūnaṁ → garunaṁ (bj, sya-all, pts-vp-pli1) ",
    "snp2.9:3.2": "niraṅkatvā → nirākatvā (?) ",
